      "text": "The four laws of thermodynamics define fundamental physical quantities (temperature, energy, and entropy) that characterize thermodynamic systems at thermal equilibrium. The laws describe how these quantities behave under various circumstances, and forbid certain phenomena (such as perpetual motion) - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laws_of_thermodynamics wikipedia]"
